-- Laine Re-Elected Chairman of French Sugar-Beet Growers Group CGB
-- B y   R u d y   R u i t e n b e r g
-- 2013-02-04T09:29:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-04/laine-re-elected-chairman-of-french-sugar-beet-growers-group-cgb.html
Eric Laine was re-elected chairman of
French sugar-beet growers’ federation Confederation Generale des
Planteurs de Betteraves by the group’s board on Feb. 1.  Laine, who is a farmer in Saint-Memmie, a municipality
outside the city of Chalons-en-Champagne east of Paris, has been
the CGB’s chairman since December 2007, the group wrote in an e-
mailed statement today.  France  is the European Union’s largest sugar-beet grower.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rudy Ruitenberg in Paris at 
 rruitenberg@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Carpenter at 
 ccarpenter2@bloomberg.net  